protocol B.

242
00:15:46.614 --> 00:15:48.115
Let's go. let's go.

243
00:15:48.248 --> 00:15:49.651
Is the green smoothie okay.

244
00:15:49.784 --> 00:15:51.786
or would you prefer
the anti-inflammatory?

245
00:15:51.920 --> 00:15:54.789
Green. Green is fine.
I'm fasting
the rest of the week.

246
00:15:59.960 --> 00:16:02.095
Tell the neuro group
I want to meet
right after this.

247
00:16:02.229 --> 00:16:04.799
- I'll take care of it.
 -You were saying you should have...

248
00:16:08.503 --> 00:16:10.471
You were saying you should have
fired Ethan sooner?

249
00:16:10.605 --> 00:16:13.908
After the paucity
of research funds in academia.

250
00:16:14.475 --> 00:16:16.845
Ethan went a little crazy
with the funds
that we had here.

251
00:16:16.977 --> 00:16:20.113
His studies grew more fringe.
more expensive.

252
00:16:20.247 --> 00:16:22.382
and they seemed
to be going nowhere.

253
00:16:23.016 --> 00:16:24.786
I started to feel that
he was taking advantage of me.

254
00:16:24.919 --> 00:16:26.386
When's the last time
you saw each other?

255
00:16:26.521 --> 00:16:28.756
I'm assuming you heard
about our confrontation.

256
00:16:29.691 --> 00:16:31.492
It was nothing. really.

257
00:16:31.992 --> 00:16:35.496
I asked Ethan
how his research was going.
and he told me to go to hell.

258
00:16:35.630 --> 00:16:37.799
-That's it?
-Ethan was unstable.

259
00:16:38.432 --> 00:16:40.969
He was using himself
as a test subject.

260
00:16:41.101 --> 00:16:42.637
You know what
he was working on?

261
00:16:44.839 --> 00:16:45.874
No.

262
00:16:53.848 --> 00:16:56.551
So you're telling me
if you had a pill that
bought you another 50 years.

263
00:16:56.684 --> 00:16:58.285
you wouldn't take it?

264
00:16:58.418 --> 00:17:01.154
Man. after the life I've had.
I'm grateful to be alive
this long.

265
00:17:01.288 --> 00:17:03.525
-Slow down.
-I can't walk any slower.

266
00:17:03.992 --> 00:17:05.025
She coming?

267
00:17:05.158 --> 00:17:06.326
Give her a chance.

268
00:17:06.794 --> 00:17:09.029
- Come on. Jackie.
I believe in you.

269
00:17:09.162 --> 00:17:10.932
-There's our girl.
-Detectives.

270
00:17:11.398 --> 00:17:14.936
I thought you might like to try
some BeneFuturum products
with our compliments.

271
00:17:15.068 --> 00:17:16.336
Thank you. Jackie.

272
00:17:18.506 --> 00:17:20.374
Is there something you want
to share with us. Jackie?

273
00:17:21.174 --> 00:17:25.178
Uh. I-I was at the conference
with Mr. Falcon and Dr. Attis.

274
00:17:25.312 --> 00:17:27.047
I... I heard them arguing.

275
00:17:27.180 --> 00:17:29.751
And it didn't go down
the way your boss said it did.
did it?

276
00:17:30.518 --> 00:17:32.820
He had to know
what Ethan was working on

277
00:17:32.954 --> 00:17:35.857
because he offered him
his old job back.
plus a huge bonus.

278
00:17:35.990 --> 00:17:38.058
and said he'd fast-track
clinical trials.

279
00:17:38.191 --> 00:17:42.229
anything Ethan wanted
for this game changer.
some formula.

280
00:17:42.362 --> 00:17:44.131
Well. what did
Ethan say to this offer?

281
00:17:44.264 --> 00:17:46.266
"Over my dead body."

282
00:17:54.509 --> 00:17:55.777
Why were you stealing?

283
00:17:56.778 --> 00:17:58.046
I was hungry.

284
00:17:58.178 --> 00:17:59.781
You ever think
about getting a job?

285
00:18:00.347 --> 00:18:04.251
I had a job. but the friend
I was working with
had to go away.

286
00:18:04.384 --> 00:18:07.055
Rafael Wexford. Correct?

287
00:18:07.187 --> 00:18:10.758
And the reason he "went away"
was because he was arrested
for murder.

288
00:18:10.892 --> 00:18:12.292
That's the truth
they decided on.

289
00:18:15.095 --> 00:18:16.463
People like you don't care.

290
00:18:17.097 --> 00:18:20.868
First thing
we need to get straight.
you don't know people like me.

291
00:18:23.871 --> 00:18:25.105
Tell me about this job.

292
00:18:28.710 --> 00:18:32.279
I was a salesman.
Handmade Turkish rugs.

293
00:18:32.412 --> 00:18:34.082
Any good?

294
00:18:34.214 --> 00:18:39.453
Well. I was moving 20 units
a week at $3.500 a unit. cash.

295
00:18:39.587 --> 00:18:40.955
Which is really
a remarkable price

296
00:18:41.089 --> 00:18:42.857
for an original.
durable work of art

297
00:18:42.991 --> 00:18:44.859
that'll be in the family
for generations.

298
00:18:46.159 --> 00:18:48.428
A quality rug makes
a statement. You might wanna--

299
00:18:48.563 --> 00:18:51.398
Mm-hmm. So you read people.
gain their trust.

300
00:18:52.100 --> 00:18:53.601
talk them out of their money.

301
00:18:54.434 --> 00:18:55.803
Well. not exactly.

302
00:18:55.937 --> 00:18:57.270
That takes insight.

303
00:18:58.305 --> 00:18:59.907
And skill.

304
00:19:00.041 --> 00:19:02.910
You and I both know
this isn't your first time
breaking the law.

305
00:19:03.443 --> 00:19:06.179
Is this how you intend
to go through life?

306
00:19:06.313 --> 00:19:08.248
<i>I remember this.</i>

307
00:19:08.983 --> 00:19:10.283
I was so afraid.

308
00:19:13.521 --> 00:19:15.222
<i>Why didn't you tell me</i>
<i>it was you?</i>

309
00:19:15.857 --> 00:19:17.992
<i>It was you who saved me.</i>

310
00:19:18.126 --> 00:19:21.161
<i>You knew</i>
<i>exactly who I was.</i>

311
00:19:24.331 --> 00:19:25.700
You knew my mother.

312
00:19:27.902 --> 00:19:30.038
Everything could have been
so different.

313
00:19:31.506 --> 00:19:33.340
You want to be taken seriously?

314
00:19:33.473 --> 00:19:35.843
You need to be
a serious person.

315
00:19:37.177 --> 00:19:39.547
You want to stop
feeling sorry for yourself?

316
00:19:40.915 --> 00:19:42.650
-Be of service.
-Be of service.

317
00:19:52.126 --> 00:19:53.528
I know this case.

318
00:19:55.495 --> 00:19:57.565
I can't seem
to get my mind clear.

319
00:19:59.534 --> 00:20:01.769
My hands are so cold.

320
00:20:13.681 --> 00:20:14.649
Amanda?

321
00:20:38.005 --> 00:20:40.407
I came down here
to look at the bodies.

322
00:20:42.176 --> 00:20:44.411
Ow.

323
00:20:44.545 --> 00:20:46.047
Someone attacked me.

324
00:20:47.181 --> 00:20:49.584
- That's a good brain
you got there.

325
00:20:50.051 --> 00:20:53.087
It's a shame
you don't really use it
for more than just getting by.

326
00:20:55.556 --> 00:20:57.792
You know. you don't know
anything about me.

327
00:20:57.925 --> 00:21:00.962
Something else is going on.
This isn't real.

328
00:21:02.630 --> 00:21:03.664
It's in my head.

329
00:21:04.632 --> 00:21:05.733
Obviously.

330
00:21:07.135 --> 00:21:09.237
But why? I got attacked...

331
00:21:09.369 --> 00:21:11.639
...hit on the head...

332
00:21:13.674 --> 00:21:15.109
I must be unconscious.

333
00:21:18.246 --> 00:21:19.279
Excellent.

334
00:21:20.248 --> 00:21:22.315
Why is it so cold?

335
00:21:22.449 --> 00:21:23.684
Figure it out.

336
00:21:24.252 --> 00:21:27.021
Oh. what?
You're gonna tell me you can't.
because life has been unfair?

337
00:21:27.155 --> 00:21:30.758
- You can't read?
People say you're stupid?

338
00:21:32.693 --> 00:21:35.096
Why were you always
so hard on me?

339
00:21:35.229 --> 00:21:39.167
Because my father's father
was hard on him.

340
00:21:39.667 --> 00:21:41.468
-He was hard on me.
-Mmm.

341
00:21:41.602 --> 00:21:43.436
And now
I'm being hard on you.

342
00:21:43.571 --> 00:21:45.006
So think.

343
00:21:45.139 --> 00:21:47.642
If you were the attacker
and you didn't want
to get caught.

344
00:21:48.276 --> 00:21:49.210
what would you do?

345
00:21:49.342 --> 00:21:50.477
I'd hide the body.

346
00:21:51.846 --> 00:21:55.016
The cold I've been feeling.
the dread.

347
00:21:55.983 --> 00:21:58.318
the whole world
closing in on me.

348
00:22:01.289 --> 00:22:02.290
I know where I am.

349
00:22:14.735 --> 00:22:18.306
Okay. Fine. Thank you. Bye.

350
00:22:18.773 --> 00:22:21.642
Are these Krista Sanderton?

351
00:22:21.776 --> 00:22:26.013
Yes. Aka Kristin Sandvale.

352
00:22:26.147 --> 00:22:27.682
They both are.

353
00:22:27.815 --> 00:22:31.052
Three years ago.
she was arrested
for check fraud. Fulton County.

354
00:22:31.185 --> 00:22:33.888
Six months later.
took a collar for slinging
counterfeit Gucci bags

355
00:22:34.021 --> 00:22:35.455
out the back of her trunk.

356
00:22:35.590 --> 00:22:37.925
-Well. so much
for being a receptionist.
-Well. she kind of was.

357
00:22:38.059 --> 00:22:41.529
Earlier this year.
she was at the front desk of
Mount Olympus Athletic Club--

358
00:22:41.662 --> 00:22:44.198
Oh. Isn't that place expensive?
People join it for the flex.

359
00:22:44.332 --> 00:22:45.700
Exactly.

360
00:22:45.833 --> 00:22:48.970
She was fired for ingratiating
herself to male club members

361
00:22:49.103 --> 00:22:51.205
and ripping off
their credit cards.

362
00:22:51.973 --> 00:22:54.775
No charges were pressed
because the club
didn't want the scandal.

363
00:22:54.909 --> 00:22:56.744
Do you think she was
scamming Ethan. though?

364
00:22:56.878 --> 00:22:58.679
It's not like his pockets
were that deep.

365
00:22:58.813 --> 00:23:00.447
I know.

366
00:23:00.581 --> 00:23:03.818
Maybe it was one of the guys
that she ripped off
coming after her.

367
00:23:03.951 --> 00:23:05.653
and Ethan was
just collateral damage?

368
00:23:05.786 --> 00:23:07.054
Hmm.

369
00:23:09.724 --> 00:23:12.026
-Have you seen Will?
-He might have gone home.

370
00:23:12.159 --> 00:23:15.730
I texted and told him
that I would cover him
if he needed another day.

371
00:23:18.199 --> 00:23:19.399
Oh. my God.

372
00:23:21.903 --> 00:23:24.639
God. you guys
are babies here.

373
00:23:24.772 --> 00:23:25.940
Hmm.

374
00:23:26.073 --> 00:23:28.943
Yeah. She had it at her house.

375
00:23:32.580 --> 00:23:33.681
How you holding up?

376
00:23:37.551 --> 00:23:41.889
You know. I guess I thought
that work would keep
my mind busy. but. um...

377
00:23:42.023 --> 00:23:43.758
Yeah. I know.

378
00:23:55.903 --> 00:24:00.608
Oh. Why do I feel so.
uh. peaceful?

379
00:24:01.609 --> 00:24:04.812
Hmm. Possibly the rise
of carbon dioxide.

380
00:24:04.946 --> 00:24:07.548
Creates a sense of euphoria.

381
00:24:08.115 --> 00:24:09.350
Right.

382
00:24:09.482 --> 00:24:11.752
The morgue drawers are closed
by a magnetic seal.

383
00:24:11.886 --> 00:24:14.322
and the cold air
creates a partial vacuum.

384
00:24:14.454 --> 00:24:18.125
I'm... I'm gonna
run out of air and suffocate.

385
00:24:18.259 --> 00:24:21.162
Yes. excellent.

386
00:24:21.295 --> 00:24:22.930
Um... Oh.

387
00:24:24.098 --> 00:24:26.033
Look at this new suit.

388
00:24:26.167 --> 00:24:27.668
-Gotta look the part.
-Hmm.

389
00:24:27.802 --> 00:24:29.469
And you will pay me back.

390
00:24:32.006 --> 00:24:33.107
That's right.

391
00:24:34.942 --> 00:24:37.578
- You bought me
my first good suit.

392
00:24:38.546 --> 00:24:41.615
-You saw something in me.
-No. no. we're not doing this.

393
00:24:41.749 --> 00:24:44.484
I mean.
would it have killed you
to invite me over to dinner?

394
00:24:45.786 --> 00:24:49.256
Ask about my life.
told me about yours?

395
00:24:49.390 --> 00:24:51.525
God. this is
a long elevator ride.

396
00:24:51.659 --> 00:24:55.029
I don't know anything
about your childhood. your mom.

397
00:24:55.162 --> 00:24:56.130
Did you go to prom?

398
00:24:56.263 --> 00:24:57.965
Did you...

399
00:24:58.099 --> 00:25:00.401
Did you get in trouble? Huh?

400
00:25:00.534 --> 00:25:01.969
You look like you might have.

401
00:25:02.103 --> 00:25:03.404
What did you expect?

402
00:25:03.537 --> 00:25:05.306
That we were gonna
go get ice cream

403
00:25:05.439 --> 00:25:07.842
and sing "Ain't No Mountain
High Enough" together?

404
00:25:07.975 --> 00:25:09.710
Yes. why not?

405
00:25:09.844 --> 00:25:12.546
I mean. we both know the words.

406
00:25:16.484 --> 00:25:17.818
You are a fool.

407
00:25:22.456 --> 00:25:23.491
Wilbur.

408
00:25:26.027 --> 00:25:27.495
What happened to you...

409
00:25:29.296 --> 00:25:33.601
I'll spend the rest of my life
making it right with you.

410
00:25:37.371 --> 00:25:40.474
Why'd you have to go looking
for The Commander alone?

411
00:25:41.842 --> 00:25:44.011
Why'd you keep so many secrets?

412
00:25:45.079 --> 00:25:46.515
I mean...

413
00:25:49.650 --> 00:25:51.252
It's my fault.
I shouldn't have--

414
00:25:51.385 --> 00:25:52.987
Hey. hey. now.

415
00:25:53.721 --> 00:25:58.692
Don't you dare take credit
for my actions. young man.

416
00:25:58.826 --> 00:26:00.227
I make my own choices.

417
00:26:02.029 --> 00:26:02.963
Yes. ma'am.

418
00:26:03.097 --> 00:26:05.199
You've only got
a couple of hours left.

419
00:26:05.332 --> 00:26:06.867
How would you like to spend it?

420
00:26:08.002 --> 00:26:09.603
I want to solve
a case with you.

421
00:26:10.838 --> 00:26:12.440
I can clear my afternoon.

422
00:26:22.983 --> 00:26:25.286
They were both strangled
with the same tubing.

423
00:26:26.387 --> 00:26:28.689
-But the marks are different.
you see?
-Mmm.

424
00:26:29.723 --> 00:26:32.326
Good. Details first.

425
00:26:32.460 --> 00:26:34.495
Most people
tell themselves a story

426
00:26:34.628 --> 00:26:38.632
and then see the details
that fit later on. Go on.

427
00:26:38.766 --> 00:26:40.634
Well. hers show more force.

428
00:26:42.236 --> 00:26:45.272
She was strangled harder.
longer.

429
00:26:45.406 --> 00:26:47.108
She fought back more.

430
00:26:48.042 --> 00:26:51.345
Or maybe she mattered more.

431
00:26:53.848 --> 00:26:55.716
But why?

432
00:26:55.850 --> 00:27:00.054
In my experience.
murder tends to be motivated
from one of three places:

433
00:27:00.187 --> 00:27:04.425
the heart. the loins.
or the hands.

434
00:27:04.559 --> 00:27:05.860
The hands?

435
00:27:05.993 --> 00:27:08.129
Boy. need I remind you
of what you did
with your hands?

436
00:27:09.564 --> 00:27:11.465
Yes. I stole.

437
00:27:11.600 --> 00:27:15.136
Exactly. This work
isn't for everyone.

438
00:27:15.970 --> 00:27:20.341
But it could bring purpose
and meaning

439
00:27:20.474 --> 00:27:23.444
in a world filled with cruelty.

440
00:27:25.746 --> 00:27:30.484
Wilbur. it could make
all that happened to you
mean something.

441
00:27:35.524 --> 00:27:37.958
I'm a doctor. Very charming.

442
00:27:38.092 --> 00:27:39.293
I like worms.

443
00:27:39.426 --> 00:27:42.631
My first wife died.
It wasn't me. it was cancer.

444
00:27:43.230 --> 00:27:45.199
Recently. I got married
to the love of Will's life.

445
00:27:46.800 --> 00:27:48.702
We're expecting a baby soon.
I'm very happy.

446
00:27:49.970 --> 00:27:53.140
Okay. Doctor.
You want to tell me
what you're doing here?

447
00:27:53.274 --> 00:27:54.308
Um...

448
00:27:55.309 --> 00:27:56.343
Will?

449
00:27:59.280 --> 00:28:00.615
I called you.

450
00:28:01.682 --> 00:28:04.051
Yes. it had
something to do with...

451
00:28:06.353 --> 00:28:08.022
with these photos.

452
00:28:08.155 --> 00:28:11.358
Right. um...
Ugh. what was it? Uh...

453
00:28:12.193 --> 00:28:15.129
Oh. Wor... Worms.

454
00:28:15.262 --> 00:28:16.631
You like worms.

455
00:28:17.131 --> 00:28:20.034
That's it. Yes. wait. we-we...

456
00:28:20.167 --> 00:28:21.902
we learned about these.
didn't we?

457
00:28:22.504 --> 00:28:27.509
Some type of flatworm.
Um. nicknamed. uh...

458
00:28:27.642 --> 00:28:28.976
Come on.

459
00:28:29.843 --> 00:28:31.812
- "Landchovies."
- Right.

460
00:28:31.946 --> 00:28:34.181
Yes. very aggressive hunters.

461
00:28:34.315 --> 00:28:36.750
They subdue their prey
by rubbing up against them.

462
00:28:36.884 --> 00:28:38.620
Yes. yes. that's what
I was trying to remember.

463
00:28:38.752 --> 00:28:41.590
They. uh...
Their skin secretes something.

464
00:28:41.722 --> 00:28:43.857
- Mmm. uh. let me think.
- Um...

465
00:28:43.991 --> 00:28:46.827
Hold on. let me think.
Uh. they're...

466
00:28:47.696 --> 00:28:48.996
Come on.

467
00:28:49.129 --> 00:28:51.232
You know this. right. because
I'm an extension of you.

468
00:28:51.365 --> 00:28:54.068
-Tetrodotoxin.
-That is a neurotoxin.

469
00:28:54.201 --> 00:28:57.071
Wait a minute.
That's what the guy
in the hazmat suit said to you.

470
00:28:57.204 --> 00:29:00.374
Yes. Yes. yes. yes.
Other animals have it too.
Starfish. newts.

471
00:29:00.508 --> 00:29:03.277
That must be what all these
pictures in Ethan's office
have in common.

472
00:29:03.410 --> 00:29:07.281
So what does
this tetrodo...
...whatever the hell do?

473
00:29:07.414 --> 00:29:08.782
Well. it depends on the amount.

474
00:29:08.916 --> 00:29:11.819
It disrupts the signals
to the muscles.
causing paralysis.

475
00:29:11.952 --> 00:29:14.221
It lowers blood pressure.
slows down breathing.

476
00:29:14.355 --> 00:29:16.056
<i>- It tends to be lethal.</i>
<i>but the--</i>

477
00:29:16.190 --> 00:29:17.458
Ooh.

478
00:29:17.592 --> 00:29:19.260
Excuse me. This thing.

479
00:29:20.027 --> 00:29:21.762
Oh. shoot.

480
00:29:21.895 --> 00:29:24.164
I need to go save some children
and make love to Angie.

481
00:29:24.298 --> 00:29:26.400
No. don't.

482
00:29:28.536 --> 00:29:30.070
I really enjoyed
seeing you. Will.

483
00:29:30.204 --> 00:29:31.706
I hope you figure this out.

484
00:29:31.839 --> 00:29:32.906
I don't want you to die.

485
00:29:33.040 --> 00:29:34.141
-Me neither.
-Okay.

486
00:29:34.275 --> 00:29:37.077
Okay. thank you. Seth.
I will try.

487
00:29:38.979 --> 00:29:40.749
Well. he was very helpful.

488
00:29:44.552 --> 00:29:48.222
Krista and I
only worked together
for a few months. but...

489
00:29:51.693 --> 00:29:53.528
No. sorry. No way was
she in love with that guy.

490
00:29:53.662 --> 00:29:55.429
I mean. we heard
they were pretty happy.

491
00:29:55.563 --> 00:29:58.932
Oh. Krista was good at that.
She could make men
believe anything.

492
00:29:59.066 --> 00:30:00.301
Like our boss. Simon.

493
00:30:00.901 --> 00:30:04.506
She told him that
waking up at 7:00 a.m.
triggered her migraines.

494
00:30:04.639 --> 00:30:06.140
so she never had
to work the opening shift.

495
00:30:06.874 --> 00:30:08.643
That girl was always
working an angle.

496
00:30:08.777 --> 00:30:10.311
She ever seem scared to you?

497
00:30:10.444 --> 00:30:12.614
Like somebody
was bothering her.
anything like that?

498
00:30:12.747 --> 00:30:15.249
Uh. no. She was fearless.

499
00:30:15.784 --> 00:30:17.818
- Too fearless. I guess.
- Mmm.

500
00:30:19.788 --> 00:30:22.923
-Where did you get that?
-Uh. the founder's a member
at the gym.

501
00:30:23.057 --> 00:30:25.392
Ward Falcon?
Did Krista know him?

502
00:30:25.527 --> 00:30:28.495
Yeah. duh. Didn't she go
to work for him or something?

503
00:30:28.630 --> 00:30:30.632
She told me that
after she got fired.

504
00:30:30.765 --> 00:30:33.601
He was paying way more
than what we made at the club.

505
00:30:33.735 --> 00:30:35.670
I'll tell Faith.

506
00:30:35.804 --> 00:30:37.104
You sit tight.

507
00:30:37.706 --> 00:30:38.972
Uh. Polaski.

508
00:30:39.106 --> 00:30:40.174
Hey. you busy?

509
00:30:40.307 --> 00:30:42.343
I have 47 seconds.
and they are all yours.

510
00:30:42.476 --> 00:30:43.844
Well. I better
make it count then.

511
00:30:43.977 --> 00:30:46.213
Um...
I don't want to be dramatic.

512
00:30:46.347 --> 00:30:48.015
but I'm a little worried
about Will.

513
00:30:48.148 --> 00:30:49.450
Yeah. why?

514
00:30:49.584 --> 00:30:50.984
Well. he's not picking up
his phone.

515
00:30:51.985 --> 00:30:54.088
He probably went home
and turned off his ringer.

516
00:30:54.221 --> 00:30:55.889
Anyway. it was
his first day back. so...

517
00:30:56.023 --> 00:30:57.759
Yeah. but we were supposed
to meet an hour ago.

518
00:30:57.891 --> 00:31:00.094
He would've texted. right?
I mean. it's just...

519
00:31:00.562 --> 00:31:02.329
I don't know.
It doesn't seem like him.

520
00:31:03.631 --> 00:31:04.699
No. it doesn't.

521
00:31:07.034 --> 00:31:09.804
See. right here. Ever since
Krista started dating Ethan.

522
00:31:09.937 --> 00:31:13.040
she was receiving
weekly payments from something
called Somni LLC.

523
00:31:13.173 --> 00:31:16.910
It's got to be a shell company.
no doubt owned by Ward Falcon.

524
00:31:17.044 --> 00:31:20.147
Mmm. So he was paying her
to steal Ethan's new formula.

525
00:31:20.280 --> 00:31:22.049
Maybe she got caught.

526
00:31:22.182 --> 00:31:24.552
Yeah. but if anyone
was gonna kill her for that.
it would have been Ethan.

527
00:31:25.285 --> 00:31:26.286
Well. then. who killed him?

528
00:31:27.589 --> 00:31:28.623
Oh.

529
00:31:29.557 --> 00:31:30.592
Hey. Angie.

530
00:31:31.860 --> 00:31:32.893
What?

531
00:31:35.028 --> 00:31:36.397
Hey. Pete. have you seen Will?

532
00:31:36.531 --> 00:31:37.998
-Has he been down here?
-No. no.

533
00:31:38.132 --> 00:31:40.167
He's missing. He had photos
of victims' bodies on his desk.

534
00:31:40.300 --> 00:31:41.770
We thought maybe
he came down here.

535
00:31:41.902 --> 00:31:43.203
What's wrong?

536
00:31:43.337 --> 00:31:45.139
I-I just got back from court
and I was about to change.

537
00:31:45.272 --> 00:31:47.274
One of the bodies is missing.

538
00:31:47.408 --> 00:31:48.643
What. like it was misplaced?

539
00:31:48.777 --> 00:31:51.613
No. no.
it was here when I left.
and now it's gone.

540
00:31:56.718 --> 00:31:58.285
How the hell does that happen?

541
00:32:04.859 --> 00:32:07.529
<i>Will. get in here.</i>
<i>We're running out of time.</i>

542
00:32:13.100 --> 00:32:14.234
Look what I found.

543
00:32:14.368 --> 00:32:15.703
Oh. yeah.

544
00:32:16.805 --> 00:32:19.306
Ethan had the same painting
in his study.

545
00:32:20.240 --> 00:32:23.944
Greenland shark. um...
That's all I know.

546
00:32:25.245 --> 00:32:27.214
Oh. come on.

547
00:32:27.347 --> 00:32:30.585
Calvin and his <i>Big Book</i>
<i>of Shark Facts</i> would slap you
if they heard you say that.

548
00:32:32.921 --> 00:32:34.321
I feel sick.

549
00:32:34.455 --> 00:32:37.491
- I know.
You're running out of oxygen.

550
00:32:39.393 --> 00:32:41.596
But. Wilbur. I need you to try.

551
00:32:45.098 --> 00:32:46.801
Yeah. Okay.

552
00:32:51.706 --> 00:32:54.141
Greenland shark.

553
00:32:54.909 --> 00:33:00.013
It can live up to 500 years
because of the cold water.
and they're slow.

554
00:33:00.147 --> 00:33:02.784
Their hearts are slow.

555
00:33:02.917 --> 00:33:05.520
The slower the heartbeat.
the longer it lasts.

556
00:33:08.623 --> 00:33:10.859
Worm toxin
slows everything down.

557
00:33:13.460 --> 00:33:17.866
Well. maybe Ethan was using it
in his sleep formula
to live longer.

558
00:33:18.465 --> 00:33:21.001
There. See?

559
00:33:22.537 --> 00:33:24.973
I'm gonna make sure
you go to college.

560
00:33:25.472 --> 00:33:26.975
Wait. what?

561
00:33:27.509 --> 00:33:30.812
No. no.
I'm-I'm no good at school.
No college would take me.

562
00:33:30.945 --> 00:33:36.016
Oh. I don't want to hear it.
You need a degree
to come work here at the GBI.

563
00:33:36.718 --> 00:33:39.486
That's where I'm headed. Here.

564
00:33:40.855 --> 00:33:43.992
- They think I should be happy...
- ...with captain.

565
00:33:45.125 --> 00:33:46.193
No.

566
00:33:46.895 --> 00:33:50.230
I'm just getting started.
and you're coming with me.

567
00:33:51.064 --> 00:33:52.165
I have a vision.

568
00:34:00.675 --> 00:34:02.409
You trying to make fun of me?

569
00:34:04.244 --> 00:34:06.581
College? GBI?

570
00:34:06.714 --> 00:34:10.919
I can't do that. okay?
Don't do this to me again.

571
00:34:11.051 --> 00:34:12.386
Wilbur...

572
00:34:13.988 --> 00:34:16.824
I'm offering you a future.

573
00:34:17.926 --> 00:34:18.893
With me.

574
00:34:19.027 --> 00:34:22.030
If I take it. you die.

575
00:34:25.432 --> 00:34:27.067
You died. Amanda.

576
00:34:27.602 --> 00:34:29.037
You died.

577
00:34:33.708 --> 00:34:34.676
Who is that?

578
00:34:34.809 --> 00:34:36.410
He's bad news. Come on.

579
00:34:40.213 --> 00:34:42.416
Come on.

580
00:34:45.987 --> 00:34:49.591
-Maybe he's here to help.
-No. He doesn't
want us together.

581
00:34:52.125 --> 00:34:55.897
What was
the first thing you saw
after you got knocked out?

582
00:34:56.564 --> 00:34:58.800
Nothing. Everyone was gone.

583
00:34:58.933 --> 00:35:01.769
You saw the man
in the hazmat suit.

584
00:35:01.903 --> 00:35:05.138
He told you
there was a neurotoxin
at the crime scene.

585
00:35:06.007 --> 00:35:08.576
Your instinct hasn't left you
just because I died.

586
00:35:08.710 --> 00:35:11.779
Or are you gonna
keep telling yourself
you can't do this without me?

587
00:35:14.749 --> 00:35:20.253
I kept waiting for this idea
of who I thought you should be.

588
00:35:23.925 --> 00:35:26.628
-I realize I never said--
-Will. it's okay.

589
00:35:26.761 --> 00:35:29.631
I know. I knew.

590
00:35:41.576 --> 00:35:43.778
Thank you for believing in me.

591
00:35:59.861 --> 00:36:03.363
There were signs of a struggle.

592
00:36:03.497 --> 00:36:04.632
Gash on his cheek.

593
00:36:10.237 --> 00:36:11.773
It was Krista.

594
00:36:12.740 --> 00:36:15.810
Broken nail.
They were fighting each other.

595
00:36:18.311 --> 00:36:21.214
Her purse.
Ethan was searching it.

596
00:36:24.986 --> 00:36:26.988
It was the formula
he was working on.

597
00:36:27.121 --> 00:36:28.656
She was stealing it.

598
00:36:29.157 --> 00:36:31.159
He strangled her in a rage.

599
00:36:31.291 --> 00:36:34.261
But the plumbers were home.
He knew he'd get caught.

600
00:36:36.531 --> 00:36:40.200
Ethan wrapped the tubing
around his own throat.

601
00:36:41.368 --> 00:36:45.673
He took enough of the formula.
it would slow his heart
to almost nothing.

602
00:36:48.042 --> 00:36:50.044
Ethan Attis was never dead.

603
00:36:51.211 --> 00:36:53.014
That's who attacked you.

604
00:36:53.147 --> 00:36:54.949
He woke up and escaped.

605
00:36:55.083 --> 00:36:56.117
No!

606
00:36:58.886 --> 00:37:00.588
-Will!
-I should have killed you.

607
00:37:11.866 --> 00:37:14.035
Wilbur Trent. come on now.

608
00:37:14.836 --> 00:37:16.904
Come on. I need you
to get in the drawer.

609
00:37:17.038 --> 00:37:18.706
-No. I'm not leaving you.
-Yes.

610
00:37:18.840 --> 00:37:21.241
Your friends will find you.
okay? They'll figure it out.

611
00:37:21.374 --> 00:37:22.877
No.

612
00:37:28.248 --> 00:37:30.317
Will. Will!

613
00:37:49.003 --> 00:37:51.873
I need you
to trust me. okay?

614
00:37:52.006 --> 00:37:53.541
You have to go. now!

615
00:37:55.176 --> 00:37:56.144
Come on.

616
00:37:56.644 --> 00:37:58.012
Okay. Come on.

617
00:37:58.146 --> 00:38:01.616
I got you. Here. Come on. Okay.

618
00:38:02.116 --> 00:38:03.851
It's time for you to let me go.

619
00:38:05.620 --> 00:38:06.821
I don't wanna leave you.

620
00:38:08.923 --> 00:38:10.423
Don't leave me please.

621
00:38:11.125 --> 00:38:13.795
I will always be with you.

622
00:38:14.629 --> 00:38:18.166
You hear me? Always.

623
00:38:19.200 --> 00:38:20.601
I love you. Wilbur.

624
00:38:21.135 --> 00:38:22.603
I love you too. Amanda.

625
00:38:40.588 --> 00:38:41.622
Will.

626
00:38:43.456 --> 00:38:46.661
Will.

627
00:38:53.601 --> 00:38:55.269
- Oxygen.
- Okay.

628
00:38:55.402 --> 00:38:56.871
Uh. we need medical...

629
00:39:17.357 --> 00:39:19.026
GBI! Don't move!

630
00:39:20.094 --> 00:39:21.863
All you had to do
was keep running.

631
00:39:21.996 --> 00:39:23.664
You just couldn't leave
your formula. could you?

632
00:39:23.798 --> 00:39:24.999
I'm not a murderer.

633
00:39:25.132 --> 00:39:26.734
All I ever wanted
was to help people.

634
00:39:26.868 --> 00:39:28.501
I loved Krista. and she...

635
00:39:29.070 --> 00:39:31.205
It all happened so fast.
I was out of my mind.

636
00:39:31.339 --> 00:39:33.908
Yet you still had
the thought to hide the goods
so no one else could find 'em.

637
00:39:34.041 --> 00:39:36.443
and you left
a GBI special agent
to suffocate and die.

638
00:39:36.577 --> 00:39:37.845
Too bad for you. he lived.

639
00:39:38.579 --> 00:39:41.182
Put it down. Now!

640
00:39:43.050 --> 00:39:44.085
Turn around.

641
00:39:46.354 --> 00:39:50.658
Ethan Attis. I'm placing you
under arrest for the murder
of Krista Sanderton

642
00:39:50.791 --> 00:39:54.061
and the attempted murder
of Special Agent Will Trent.
Let's go.

643
00:39:59.567 --> 00:40:01.035
You solved the case
while unconscious.

644
00:40:01.168 --> 00:40:02.236
and you're making
good progress.

645
00:40:02.370 --> 00:40:04.372
You should be
going home later today.

646
00:40:04.505 --> 00:40:05.773
You're very lucky.

647
00:40:06.540 --> 00:40:08.776
I don't know about that. Um...

648
00:40:10.244 --> 00:40:12.780
This year has felt like
all my luck has run out.

649
00:40:14.615 --> 00:40:15.950
I know that kind of year.

650
00:40:19.320 --> 00:40:20.688
Your first wife?

651
00:40:20.821 --> 00:40:22.489
Mmm.

652
00:40:23.524 --> 00:40:26.093
You know. with my job.
I'm around death all the time.

653
00:40:27.427 --> 00:40:29.864
But nothing prepared me
for when she got sick.

654
00:40:30.497 --> 00:40:35.736
I just... I had to watch her
get sicker and weaker.
and I couldn't stop it.

655
00:40:35.870 --> 00:40:38.239
And then she was gone.
and my life was over.

656
00:40:40.107 --> 00:40:41.342
But then I had this year.

657
00:40:44.545 --> 00:40:46.280
Things can turn on a dime.

658
00:40:47.381 --> 00:40:48.983
And sometimes
even for the better.

659
00:40:50.418 --> 00:40:53.220
Yeah. I guess so.

660
00:41:14.308 --> 00:41:16.277
Oh.

661
00:41:23.417 --> 00:41:25.319
Where'd you come from.
little angel?

662
00:41:41.035 --> 00:41:43.304
Oh. my gosh. This is you?

663
00:41:44.605 --> 00:41:46.374
You were so cute.

664
00:41:46.507 --> 00:41:48.676
Look. you're actually smiling.

665
00:41:55.316 --> 00:41:56.350
What's this?

666
00:42:09.897 --> 00:42:11.032
A promise.

666
00:42:12.305 --> 00:43:12.477
